headline: How the Narrative Around Corteva Is Shifting After the Announced Business Split
summary: Corteva’s consensus analyst price target has been modestly reduced, shifting from $79.81 to $79.05 per share, as the market digests the company’s decision to split into two public entities. This change reflects a careful balancing of optimism about Corteva’s core strengths and caution regarding the uncertainties tied to the breakup.
